docs.abstract: Patty Mills, a key reserve for the San Antonio Spurs, said he developed an emotional shield from a lifetime of racial abuse, but he is using the platform of the N.B.A.’s restart to speak out against racism.
docs.snippet: Patty Mills, a key reserve for the San Antonio Spurs, said he developed an emotional shield from a lifetime of racial abuse, but he is using the platform of the N.B.A.’s restart to speak out against racism.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. — There were a few must-pack accessories for Patty Mills of the San Antonio Spurs for his stay at Walt Disney World. Mills brought a stack of books on Black history in the United States and his native Australia. He made sure to carefully transport his favorite flat-brimmed hat, which bears two flags representing Australia’s Indigenous populations.

headline.main: ‘The Better I Got in Sports, the Worse the Racism Got’
headline.print_headline: A Star With a Trusty Jump Shot,  And a Stage to Share His Story

docs.abstract: Almost all dance in the United States has gone virtual. But Kaatsbaan will fill the void, hosting its first-ever festival.
docs.snippet: Almost all dance in the United States has gone virtual. But Kaatsbaan will fill the void, hosting its first-ever festival.
docs.lead_paragraph: TIVOLI, N.Y. — This summer, as stages around the country lie empty and unused, Kaatsbaan, in Tivoli, N.Y., will be something precious and rare: one of the few places in America where dancers will be performing live, in person, in front of a living and breathing, if well-distanced and masked audience.

headline.main: In the Hudson Valley: Live Dancers, Real Sweat, Natural Beauty
headline.print_headline: At a Haven,  Filling the Void

docs.abstract: Holland Cotter masks up on the Lower East Side and SoHo; Jillian Steinhauer discovers eco-feminist art taking root in Chelsea.
docs.snippet: Holland Cotter masks up on the Lower East Side and SoHo; Jillian Steinhauer discovers eco-feminist art taking root in Chelsea.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the New York art world, normal is still a long hike down the pike, but some of the city’s galleries are tiptoeing in that direction with socially distanced reopenings.

headline.main: As Galleries Reopen, Two Critics Find Rewards Eclipse the Angst

byline.original: By Holland Cotter and Jillian Steinhauer

docs.abstract: Maya Stovall, known for her dance performances in public spaces, shares a new artwork.
docs.snippet: Maya Stovall, known for her dance performances in public spaces, shares a new artwork.
docs.lead_paragraph: In this new series, The Artists, an installment of which will publish every day this week and regularly thereafter, T will highlight a recent or little-shown work by a Black artist, along with a few words from that artist, putting the work into context. First up is a piece by Maya Stovall, who is best known for her dance performances in public spaces, as documented in her “Liquor Store Theater” video series, which will screen this summer as part of the citywide digital-art exhibition “Art Mile Detroit.”

headline.main: A Retelling of American History — in Neon

docs.abstract: During the pandemic, people are venturing deeper into the city’s forests, wetlands and grasslands, just as budget cuts threaten the spaces’ upkeep.
docs.snippet: During the pandemic, people are venturing deeper into the city’s forests, wetlands and grasslands, just as budget cuts threaten the spaces’ upkeep.
docs.lead_paragraph: A few weeks into the coronavirus pandemic, Steve Maing, his partner and their 2-year-old daughter, Rosie, discovered the spot that would make their life in locked-down New York bearable.

headline.main: Stir-Crazy New Yorkers Discovered an Idyllic Spot. Will They Trample It?
headline.print_headline: Stir-Crazy New Yorkers Find an Idyllic Spot. Will They Trample It?

docs.abstract: New York is finally giving its Police Department the scrutiny it deserves.
docs.snippet: New York is finally giving its Police Department the scrutiny it deserves.
docs.lead_paragraph: In New York, a 1-year-old boy was fatally shot over the weekend, one of the latest victims in a surge of violence that has rattled an already traumatized city. As of Monday, New York City had had 634 shootings this year, up from 394 at the same time last year, according to Police Department data.

headline.main: The N.Y.P.D. Has Rejected Reform for Decades. It Can’t Anymore.

docs.abstract: The shooting comes during a dispute between Mayor Lori Lightfoot and President Trump, who had said he would send federal agents to the city as it contends with violence.
docs.snippet: The shooting comes during a dispute between Mayor Lori Lightfoot and President Trump, who had said he would send federal agents to the city as it contends with violence.
docs.lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Fourteen people were shot on Tuesday evening near a funeral home on the South Side of Chicago, an episode of the kind of urban violence that President Trump has made a cornerstone of his re-election campaign.

headline.main: 14 People Are Shot Near Chicago Funeral Home

byline.original: By Robert Chiarito and Will Wright

docs.abstract: Greg Selkoe is leaving the successful esports conglomerate to start a new venture that’s less “frat house” and more diverse.
docs.snippet: Greg Selkoe is leaving the successful esports conglomerate to start a new venture that’s less “frat house” and more diverse.
docs.lead_paragraph: FaZe Clan, an esports lifestyle conglomerate, helped turn gamers into a new class of social media influencers. Now, several top executives behind FaZe Clan are leaving to start a competing organization called XSET.

headline.main: FaZe Clan President Departs: ‘It’s Time for Gaming to Clean Up Its Act’
headline.print_headline: ‘It’s Time for Gaming to Clean Up Its Act’

docs.snippet: If convicted, the two residents of Martinez, Calif., could face up to a year in jail, prosecutors say.
docs.lead_paragraph: Two white people in California were charged on Tuesday with a hate crime and other offenses after video appeared to show them vandalizing a Black Lives Matter mural on July 4, officials said.

headline.main: 2 People Charged With Hate Crime After Black Lives Matter Mural Is Vandalized

docs.abstract: Africans are increasingly pushing to hold police agencies to account and “decolonize” the repressive institutions they inherited from colonial rulers.
docs.snippet: Africans are increasingly pushing to hold police agencies to account and “decolonize” the repressive institutions they inherited from colonial rulers.
docs.lead_paragraph: NAIROBI, Kenya — Kenyan and American protesters knelt outside the United States Embassy in Nairobi one morning last month, outraged at George Floyd’s killing and the racism and brutality they saw across the Atlantic. But they were also furious about police abuses at home, in Kenya.

headline.main: George Floyd’s Killing Prompts Africans to Call for Police Reform at Home
headline.print_headline: Floyd’s Killing Prompts Africans to Seek Police Reform in Their Countries

byline.original: By Abdi Latif Dahir, Ruth Maclean and Lynsey Chutel
